<TITLE> Serve nation with patriotism, Iajuddin tells graduates </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com)  President Iajuddin Ahmed said Tuesday that universities were illustrious institutions that played a catalytic role in tuning society. The President was addressing the first convocation of Bangladesh University at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre in the capital. While paying homage to the language martyrs of 1952 at the outset of his speech, he urged the students to serve the nation with utmost devotion and innate patriotism, and called upon the university authorities to focus on grooming the innate intellect of students by ensuring them quality education. "You must strive to improve at every stage of your life," he told the students. "It is your moral responsibility to demonstrate the highest degree of personal honesty and integrity in your professional arena," the president added. He said that the role of universities was of utmost importance to the society and asked the authorities to ensure quality education for the students. Universities cultivate an environment that produce competent and honest leadership and instill self- respect, honor and dignity in students who hold the key to the nation's destiny. The president congratulated the graduate students, their guardians and the university authority on their efforts while urging the "scholarly section" of society to uphold educational values by prioritising national interest. bdnew
